e%20to%20devote%20all%20my%20attention%20to%20my%20son%20when%20he%20was%20awake%2C%20and%20pull%20out%20my%20laptop%20to%20work%20while%20he%20slept.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20reality%20of%20being%20self-employed%20as%20a%20new%20mom%20was%20not%20what%20I%20had%20imagined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228196dc78-af3e-4a50-82d2-335a790db836%5C%22%3EI%20was%20exhausted%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20running%20on%20empty%20all%20the%20time%2C%20exhausted%20from%20sleepless%20nights.%20I%20didn't%20know%20what%20I%20was%20doing%20with%20parenting%2C%20as%20I%20had%20never%20done%20it%20before%2C%20and%20often%20felt%20I%20was%20doing%20it%20all%20wrong.%20I%20adored%20my%20son%20even%20more%20than%20I%20had%20imagined%20I%20would%2C%20and%20not%20being%20with%20him%20while%20I%20worked%20constantly%20pulled%20at%20my%20heartstrings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20from%20this%20state%20that%20I%20then%20tried%20to%20work%2C%20attempting%20to%20be%20at%20clients'%20full-time%20disposal.%20Even%20though%20I%20knew%20about%20marketing%2C%20I%20didn't%20fully%20take%20into%20account%20the%20amount%20of%20work%20or%20the%20number%20of%20non-billable%20hours%20I'd%20be%20working%20as%20a%20self-employed%20individual.%20As%20opposed%20to%20working%20for%20a%20corporate%20company%2C%20I%20was%20the%20sole%20person%20responsible%20for%20every%20aspect%20of%20the%20business.%20It%20was%20all%20on%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20keen%20on%20putting%20my%20son%20in%20a%20day%20care%20to%20save%20us%20a%20bit%20of%20money%2C%20I%20tried%20to%20build%20the%20business%20with%20him%20around%20most%20of%20the%20time%2C%20save%20for%20a%20few%20hours%20a%20week%20when%20my%20mom%20or%20sister%20would%20have%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20on%20a%20hamster%20wheel%20from%20the%20moment%20I%20woke%20up%2C%20becoming%20more%20and%20more%20exhausted%20as%20I%20tried%20to%20work%20as%20if%20I%20didn't%20have%20a%20child%2C%20and%20parent%20as%20if%20I%20didn't%20have%20a%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E