ften%20considered%20the%20underdog%20of%20the%20Big%20Four%20professional%20services%20firms%2C%20being%20both%20the%20youngest%20and%20the%20smallest%20by%20global%20revenue%20and%20number%20of%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPartners%20hold%20a%20stake%20in%20the%20firm%2C%20giving%20them%20a%20vote%20in%20key%20decisions%20and%20a%20share%20of%20distributable%20profits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20payouts%20were%20up%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-four-consulting-senior-leaders-exodus-leave-for-startups-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20number%20of%20senior%20leaders%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20KPMG%20continues%20to%20slowly%20shrink.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20total%20number%20of%20partners%20dropped%20by%20six%20in%20the%202025%20calendar%20year%2C%20according%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20analysis%20of%20publicly%20available%20data.%20Partner%20numbers%20have%20declined%20for%20at%20least%20the%20last%20four%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENonetheless%2C%20the%20firm's%20results%20placed%20its%20partners%20above%20rivals%20at%20PwC%20and%20EY%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPwC%20UK%20partner%20pay%20remained%20largely%20flat%20in%20its%202025%20financial%20year%2C%20with%20partners%20receiving%20%C2%A3865%2C000%2C%20or%20%241.19%20million.%20At%20EY%2C%20partner%20payouts%20were%20%C2%A3787%2C000%2C%20just%20over%20%241%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeloitte%20remains%20the%20most%20lucrative%20for%20those%20at%20the%20top%20levels%20of%20the%20Big%20Four%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20paying%20its%20partners%20%C2%A31.05%20million%2C%20or%20%241.4%20million%2C%20in%20its%202025%20financial%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20KPMG%20UK%20reported%20annual%20revenue%20of%20%C2%A33.6%20billion%20(%244.9%20billion)%2C%20up%202%25%20from%20the%20previous%20year.%20The%20results%20include%20the%20firm's%20Switzerland%20branch%20following%20its%202024%20merger%20with%20the%20UK%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKPMG's%20UK%20audit%20and%20tax%20and%20l